      <h2>Third Party Usage</h2>
      <p>base html is <a href="http://html5boilerplate.com/" title="link out to html5 boilerplate site">HTML5 Boilerplate</a> v 4.0.2.</p>
      <p>base javascript is <a href="http://jquery.com" title="link out to jquery home page">jquery.js</a> v 1.8.2. <a href="http://jquery.com/download/" title="link out to jquery home page">Download it here</a>.</p>
      <p>Modal javascript is <a href="http://projects.nickstakenburg.com/lightview" title="link out to lightview">lightview.js</a> v 3.2.7.</p>
      <p>Pinterest style box stacking javascript is <a href="http://masonry.desandro.com/" title="link out to masonry home page">jquery.Masonry.js </a> v2.1.06. Great supporting articles: <a href="http://designshack.net/articles/css/masonry/" title="link out to article">Three Super Easy Ways to Pull Off a Masonry Layout</a>, and <a href="http://www.netmagazine.com/tutorials/get-started-jquery-masonry" title="link out to article">Get started with jQuery Masonry</a>.</p>
      <p>Plan to include responsive design, hand rolled, with media queries. Need to research pixel width break points for mobile devices and tablets. May base this off of <a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/" title="link out to bootstrap">twitter bootstrap</a> for reference.</p>
      
